column19: {"Strategy":"went from bottom anti-clock wise because it seemed the bottom and the right were the easiest to decipher, the top was reasonably easy and the left was mostly a guess. not focusing on the dots and almost trying to look through the whole circle
{"Strategy":"looked at the edge for the easy ones and the middle for the harder ones"}
{"Strategy":"there was a pattern to which way they were going  when it changed it took a bit to see the next pattern"}
{"Strategy":"the most obvious first or left to right bottom to top"}
{"Strategy":"I went clockwise starting from '12', then by the 11th attempt i reliased there was a pettern and started presssing the same thing each time "}
{"Strategy":"Process of elimination; look for the easiest, start there and move onto next easiest"}
{"Strategy":"the bottom and the right were easier to read"}
{"Strategy":"I noticed the top one always moved in one direction so i tried that direction for  them all clockwise"}
{"Strategy":"Looking at the dots closest to the right of the circle, to see which way they were going."}
{"Strategy":"button mash until done, start at the right "}
{"Strategy":"start at top, then left, right, bottom"}

{"Strategy":"watching the background dots, not the ones moving randomly to try and determine which direction they were going. I went clockwise each time except for once, the one time I didn't, I only completed 1 task."}
{"Strategy":"the ones on the sides seemed to be more consistently obvious, so I went for them first. The top one always had the most mistakes so I did that last"}

{"Strategy":"The right and left seemed clearer than the top and bottom so I started with those because I knew I could almost always get them right which would save time and maximise how many I could complete in total"}
{"Strategy":"determined a pattern towards the end of the trials"}
{"Strategy":"I just picked any random circle in order to save time, instead of wasting time thinking about which to choose."}
{"Strategy":"the bottom right and top were fairly easy so did those first and then just guessed with the remaining time on the left one"}
{"Strategy":"top, left, right, bottom (in order of least chaotic to most chaotic)"}
{"Strategy":"looking at the dots behind the main focus poin"}
{"Strategy":"Worked out they were all X after a while"}
{"Strategy":"Looked at the dots for a split second because making a decision"}

{"Strategy":"I started the first 15 trials by moving around the compass regardless of difficulty but changed strategy to checking all points to find the easier squares and work my way up in difficulty. "}
{"Strategy":"picked the ones i could see the direction the dots were going "}
{"Strategy":"Right (x), seemed to be very common, I hit it often without checking then just mashed either key or alternated between them if I got it wrong."}
{"Strategy":"Looking for change of movement direction when selecting "}
{"Strategy":"Looking at the dots that seemed to be going slower and did them first"}
{"Strategy":"after round 10 they were all left... or maybe before but that was when i realised. my mouse played up during round 10 and after that I went all left"}
{"Strategy":"eyeball which shows clearly the direction of the dots"}
{"Strategy":"Quickly recognising the patters to look out for - i.e. my eye noticing the block of circles and singling in on them"}
{"Strategy":"when I got the answer wrong, I would press on the Z & X keys alternatively to get it right on time"}

{"Strategy":"Looked at all four together rather than individually to see which were moving right and which were moving left. Had to watch the see if the direction changed when you clicked on it but very little time to do so"}
{"Strategy":"looked at which ones were easy to identify which direction"}
{"Strategy":"I tried to do the circles that were more straight forward first and then followed with the more tricky ones "}
{"Strategy":"I tried to do the circles that were more straight forward first and then followed with the more tricky ones "}
{"Strategy":"Trial and error, before a pattern emerged"}
{"Strategy":"Focusing on the centre of the circle, I could majority of the time see the change if there was one."}
{"Strategy":"completing the sets with the slowest moving balls first"}
{"Strategy":"Started with the top one 90% of the time but occasionally picked the one with most obvious direction 1st."}

{"Strategy":"whichever i noticed moving in a singular direction first. i also focused slightly behind the laptop screen to see where the dots were generally moving rather than focusing directly on the dots"}
{"Strategy":"Blurred eyes a little rather than direct focus"}
{"Strategy":"Focused with eyes using a type of blurry vision"}
